Commentary Text: Mishra to Pollard, out Lbw!! Misread googly. Trapped on the right knee roll. And plumb. Wow, this collapse is getting real. Commentary Text: Stoinis to de Kock, out Caught by Pant!! Edged and gone! Pant persisted with Stoinis and it's paid dividends. 129.7kph, another cutter from a short of length, goes across the left-hander and de Kock throws his bat at it without any feet movement. The ball moved away with a bit of extra cover. The batsman looked to batter it through the covers with an angled blade and only managed an outside nick. Easy grab for the Delhi captain and the Capitals have the early breakthrough. de Kock c Pant b Stoinis 1(4)

Commentary Text: Pollard to Smith, out Lbw!! Pollard does break the partnership - Smith has a look at his partner, but this was as plumb as it gets. Dhawan knew it, Smith knew it and off he goes. On a length and at the stumps, skidded through and stayed a bit low, Smith made it worse for himself by shuffling across and then missed it completely. Struck bang in front of middle, was going on and hitting the leg-stump. Pollard is chuffed to bits, he believes and perhaps MI believe as well. Smith lbw b Pollard 33(29) [4s-4]

Commentary Text: Jayant Yadav to Prithvi Shaw, out Caught&Bowled!! No doubt about this one though - a clean catch and Jayant celebrates with gutso, Shaw has been dismissed cheaply once again. Pushed through just outside off - Shaw was jabbing with hard hands, thought about checking his shot at the last moment, but didn't soften his hands as he did so, punched right back at the bowler who completed a tumbling catch. MI could have had Dhawan in the last over, but they will not complain about getting Shaw. Prithvi Shaw c and b Jayant Yadav 7(5) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Boult to Dhawan, no run, that's a superb catch from Hardik, failed with the bat, but makes his presence felt on the field - on a good length and a hint of straightening with the angle - Dhawan was looking to work it to the on-side, closed the bat-face and the ball looped off the leading edge, down towards cover. Hardik rushed forward, dived in front and then did he get his hands underneath the ball? Or did it bounce in front of him - the third umpire is having several looks, will Dhawan get the benefit of doubt? Hardik was in no doubt as he started celebrating immediately, but none of the angles look conclusive enough. Dhawan, on his part has gone nowhere. Is his fingers underneath the ball? Well, the third umpire certainly didn't think so - NOT OUT flashes the big screen. There was no soft signal from the on-field umpires, so the third umpire did go with whatever he could get from the TV relays. Think, it's a fair call in the end
